<item>
            <title>[HBASE-10790] make assembly:single as default in pom.xml</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-10790</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Now to compile a HBase tar release package, we should use&lt;br/&gt;
the cmd: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
 mvn clean &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; assembly:single
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;, which is not convenient. We can make assembly:single as a default option and run the assembly plugin in maven package phase. Then we can just use the cmd &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt; mvn clean &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; to get a release package.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Other suggestions are welcomed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12702385">HBASE-10790</key>
